&quot;In winter 1985, the Florida Folklife Program ... contracted with two folklorists to conduct a folk arts survey of the St. Johns River basin in northeastern Florida.   Folklorists Mary Anne McDonald and Kathleen Figgen conducted the survey from January - March, 1985.  Documentation compiled in the survey was used to prepare and present the &quot;St. Johns River Basin Folklife Area&quot; at the 1985 Florida Folk Festival.

   &quot;Figgen focused particularly on  the relatively recent presence of Mexicans and Mexican Americans who formed a significant portion of the labor force for the fern industry in and around Seville <i>(&quot;Little Mexico&quot;</i>) in the heart of the <i>&quot;fern belt&quot;</i> in Central Florida.&quot;
